<br>
 Dear anon <br><br>
Re: WHO'S IN CONTROL HERE CAPT? <br><br>
CENSORSHIP, of what we share here? Then why have a dialog? If an individual wants to post as you have it only reveals the hatred, abuse, and contempt we once faced upon our return from duty and which we face again here as you have so eloquently here substantiated.<br><br>
Let the educators, students and the public desiring to know about the true Vietnam veteran who fought the war see what individuals like you and others have posted here, against those who served in an unpopular war. Why delete how an individual feels against those who served their country with honor? <br><br>
The true intregrity of this site rest upon NO CENSORSHIP, no deletion, if you post let it stand. I have not regretted anything I have posted here. <br><br>
We have been pinned down behind our own country’s rice paddy dikes for far too long. <br><br>
APPRECIATION FOR THE SITE<br>
I very much appreciate what the webmaster here has provided and have thanked him for it. But if the site is to be believed it must stand as posted without editorial comment or deletion from anyone who regrets what they have posted. Even as you have mentioned Mr. Anon certain individuals do know “how to get your (veterans) goat.” <br>
They have done it for years and even our inflamed response is evidence of the repressed resentment we have had to harbor and endure silently for years. We have been pinned down in America’s own rice paddy for years but now we have begun to arise from that false guilt heaved upon us and Marc’s site here and others are beginning to give us that voice and for that I am truly grateful. <br><br>
But deleting something once said may be erased from this site but it still rings loud in the shadows those words left behind. How loud does this word ring?<br><br>
DELETED.<br>
Wed Dec 3 0:14:22 US/Eastern 1997 <br><br>
I am Cook Barela and those are my thoughts.<br>

